WEBVTT

00:00:01.260 --> 00:00:05.259
Our text today is discussing hospitality,

00:00:05.259 --> 00:00:10.259
and as we know hospitality includes generously giving to others.

00:00:10.259 --> 00:00:14.259
But you may have noted that our comments makes a very profound statement.

00:00:14.259 --> 00:00:21.260
It says that hospitality is one of the finest antidotes to loneliness.

00:00:21.260 --> 00:00:23.260
Have you ever been lonely?

00:00:23.260 --> 00:00:25.260
Really lonely.

00:00:25.260 --> 00:00:27.260
Loneliness can be quite painful.

00:00:27.260 --> 00:00:32.259
As we know, it's possible to be lonely even when we're surrounded by people.

00:00:32.259 --> 00:00:34.259
One writer stated,

00:00:34.259 --> 00:00:36.259
Solitude is pleasant.

00:00:36.259 --> 00:00:38.259
Loneliness is not.

00:00:38.259 --> 00:00:42.259
Another described loneliness is being like being in the rain,

00:00:42.259 --> 00:00:46.259
and the sky holds nothing but the promise of more clouds.

00:00:46.259 --> 00:00:50.259
One sister described the feeling of loneliness as slipping down a deep well,

00:00:50.259 --> 00:00:54.259
and the further she slipped, the darker things became.

00:00:55.259 --> 00:01:00.259
So what can help us to deal with loneliness before we sink too deep?

00:01:00.259 --> 00:01:02.259
What can help us start climbing back out of that well

00:01:02.259 --> 00:01:06.260
or pushing those clouds out into the sky?

00:01:06.260 --> 00:01:14.260
Well, as our text says, hospitality, generosity, giving is one of the finest antidotes to loneliness.

00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:16.260
Now, why is that?

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:20.260
Well, let's consider three scriptural principles as to why that is the case.

00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:22.260
And we'll see why this is true.

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:25.260
Look first at Acts chapter 20 and verse 35.

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:27.260
Let's read that together.

00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:29.260
Acts chapter 20 and verse 35,

00:01:29.260 --> 00:01:32.260
and we'll see our first promise.

00:01:32.260 --> 00:01:33.260
And here it says,

00:01:33.260 --> 00:01:34.260
I have shown you in all things

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:36.260
that by working hard in this way,

00:01:36.260 --> 00:01:38.260
you must assist those who are weak.

00:01:38.260 --> 00:01:42.260
And must keep in mind the words of the Lord Jesus when He Himself said,

00:01:42.260 --> 00:01:47.260
there's more happiness in giving than there is in receiving.

00:01:47.260 --> 00:01:52.260
So our first point is very simply that giving makes us happy.

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:55.260
Now, the apostle Paul here is quoting Jesus

00:01:55.260 --> 00:02:00.260
and you notice Jesus was not saying that we give when we are happy

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:02.260
